<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-03-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-03-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="780" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d780">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Moffat</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Bluefields</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-03-09"><hi rend="italic">March 9,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>M. Moffat reports that he has communicated department’s telegram of March
                            8, 8 p.m., to Gen. Estrada, who has submitted the proposed peace bases
                            to Madriz by telegraph, urging his acceptance.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>